TableCellCollection Class

Definition

Encapsulates a collection of TableHeaderCell and TableCell objects that make up a row in a Table control. This class cannot be inherited.

In this Article

[System.ComponentModel.Editor("System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.TableCellsCollectionEditor, System.Design, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b03f5f7f11d50a3a", typeof(System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditor))]
public sealed class TableCellCollection : System.Collections.IList

Remarks

Use this class to programmatically manage a collection of TableCell objects that make up a row in a Table control. This class is commonly used to add or remove cells from a row in a Table control.

Note

A Table control contains a Rows collection that represents a collection of TableRow objects. Each TableRow represents an individual row in the table and contains a Cells collection that represents a collection of TableCell objects. These TableCell objects represent the individual cells in the table. To get an individual cell, you must first get a TableRow from the Rows collection of a Table control. You can then get a TableCell from the Cells collection of the TableRow.

Properties

Count

Gets the number of TableCell objects in the TableCellCollection.

public int Count { get; }
Value
Int32

The number of TableCell objects in the TableCellCollection. The default is 0.

Remarks

Use this property to determine the number of cells in the TableCellCollection. The Count property is often used when iterating through the collection to determine the upper bound.

IsReadOnly

Gets a value indicating whether the TableCellCollection is read-only.

public bool IsReadOnly { get; }
Value
Boolean

false for all cases.

Remarks

This property always returns false to indicate that the TableCellCollection can be written to in all cases.

IsSynchronized

Gets a value indicating whether access to the TableCellCollection is synchronized (thread-safe).

public bool IsSynchronized { get; }
Value
Boolean

false for all cases.

Remarks

This property is derived from System.Collections.ICollection and is overridden to always return false.

For more information on the IsSynchronized property, see the IsSynchronized property of the System.Collections.ICollection interface.

Gets a TableCell from the TableCellCollection at the specified index.

public System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell this[int index] { get; }
index
Int32

An ordinal index value that specifies the TableCell to return.

Value
TableCell

A TableCell that represents an element in the TableCellCollection.

Remarks

Use this indexer to get an individual TableCell in the TableCellCollection at the specified index using simple array notation.

SyncRoot

Gets the object that can be used to synchronize access to the TableCellCollection.

public object SyncRoot { get; }
Value
System.Object

An object that can be used to synchronize access to the collection.

Remarks

The object returned in this implementation is the TableCellCollection itself.

For more information on the SyncRoot property, see the SyncRoot property of the System.Collections.ICollection interface.

Methods

Appends the specified TableCell to the end of the TableCellCollection.

public int Add (System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell cell);
cell
TableCell

The TableCell to add to the collection.

Returns

The index number of the TableCell.

Remarks

AddAt(Int32,TableCell)

Adds the specified TableCell to the TableCellCollection at the specified index location.

public void AddAt (int index, System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell cell);
index
Int32

The location in the TableCellCollection at which to add the TableCell.

cell
TableCell

The TableCell to add to the TableCellCollection.

Remarks

Use this method to insert the specified TableCell in a TableCellCollection at the specified index.

AddRange(TableCell[])

Appends the TableCell objects from the specified array to the end of the collection.

public void AddRange (System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell[] cells);
cells
TableCell[]

The array containing the TableCell objects to add to the collection.

Exceptions
ArgumentNullException

The value of the cells parameter is null.

Remarks

Use the AddRange method to append the TableCell objects from the specified array to the collection. This method is commonly used when you are constructing a row of a table. To construct a row of a table, first create an array of TableCell objects to represent the cells of the row. Next, use the AddRange method, passing the array as an argument, to add the TableCell objects to the collection.

Clear()

Removes all TableCell objects from the TableCellCollection.

public void Clear ();

Remarks

Use this method to remove all TableCell objects from the TableCellCollection and set the Count property to 0.

Note

This method removes the TableCell objects from the TableCellCollection, but it does not remove the TableRow from the Table control. Be sure to also remove the TableRow if you want to completely remove a row from the table.

CopyTo(Array,Int32)

Copies the items from the TableCellCollection to the specified Array, starting with the specified index in the Array.

public void CopyTo (Array array, int index);
array
Array

A zero-based Array that receives the copied items from the TableCellCollection.

index
Int32

The first index in the specified Array to receive the items.

Remarks

Use this method to copy the contents of the TableCellCollection into the specified System.Array starting at the specified index.

Note

The array parameter must be a zero-based System.Array.

GetCellIndex(TableCell)

Returns a value that represents the index of the specified TableCell from the TableCellCollection.

public int GetCellIndex (System.Web.UI.WebControls.TableCell cell);
cell
TableCell

The TableCell to get the index of in the TableCellCollection.

Returns
Int32

The index of the specified TableCell within the TableCellCollection. The default is -1, which indicates that a match has not been found.

Remarks

Use this method to determine the index of the specified TableCell in the TableCellCollection. If the specified TableCell is not found, an index of -1 is returned.

GetEnumerator()

Returns a IEnumerator implemented object that contains all TableCell objects in the TableCellCollection.

public System.Collections.IEnumerator GetEnumerator ();
Returns
IEnumerator

A IEnumerator implemented object that contains all TableCell objects within the TableCellCollection.

Remarks

Use this method to create a System.Collections.IEnumerator implemented object that can be iterated through easily to get each item in the TableCellCollection.

Use the Current property to get the item currently pointed to in the collection.

Use the MoveNext method to move to the next item in the collection.

Use the Reset method to move the enumerator back to the initial position.

Note

The MoveNext method must be called after creating a System.Collections.IEnumerator implemented object or after using the Reset method to move the enumerator to the first item in the collection. Otherwise, the item represented by the Current property is undefined.
